      "question": "Is the intervention of an ambulance in Belgium free?",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Ambulance services in Belgium are not entirely free. The cost depends on whether the situation involves emergency medical assistance or non-urgent medical transportation."
        },
        {
                          "type": "image",
                          "url": "https://rtleng.rosselcdn.net/sites/default/files/dpistyles_v2/rtl_16_9_644w/2024/08/14/node_727555/3775198/public/2024/08/14/ambulance_flandre.jpeg?itok=d5oz_Dms1723621259"
                 },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "### Emergency Medical Assistance\n- When you call **112** for a person in distress, an ambulance or Medical Emergency Group (MUG) team is dispatched to assess, treat, and transport the patient to the hospital.\n- **Cost:**\n  - Patients pay a legally fixed fee for ambulance interventions, even if they decide not to be transported.\n  - Health insurance does **not** reimburse this fee.\n  - No additional costs may be charged beyond the fixed fee.\n- The MUG team provides life-saving interventions and stabilizes the patient before hospital transport.\n  - The costs for the MUG doctor are fully reimbursed by health insurance.\n  - Some other charges may be partially borne by the patient."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "### Non-Urgent Medical Transportation\n- Non-urgent medical transportation is planned medical-sanitized transport, such as for kidney dialysis or a scheduled hospital admission.\n- **Cost:**\n  - This service is not reimbursed by health insurance.\n  - Some health insurance funds or hospitalization insurance may partially cover the costs. Check with your insurance provider for details.\n  - Significant price differences exist between transport companies. Companies should disclose a maximum tariff when you book the service, and this tariff should be displayed in the ambulance.\n- If no pricing information is provided, complaints can be filed with the company or your health insurance fund."
