{
  "question": "What is the Income Guarantee for the Elderly (IGO) in Belgium, and how can you apply for it?",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The Income Guarantee for the Elderly (IGO) is a financial benefit provided to individuals who have reached the legal retirement age but do not have sufficient means to support themselves. It ensures a basic level of income for elderly residents in Belgium."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Eligibility Criteria\nTo qualify for the IGO, the following conditions must be met:\n- **Financial Means:** Your total resources, including those of your spouse or legal partner, must fall below a certain threshold. A detailed assessment is conducted to determine this.\n- **Age:** You must have reached the legal retirement age.\n- **Nationality:** You must be a Belgian citizen or in an equivalent situation.\n- **Residence:** Your main residence must be in Belgium, and you must live there continuously without interruption.\n\nFor more details on the calculation of resources and income thresholds, visit the website of the Federal Pension Service."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Application Procedure\nIn most cases, you do not need to apply for the IGO. The process starts automatically if you:\n- Apply for a pension from the Federal Pension Service, and your pension amount is below the minimum threshold.\n- Already receive a pension and reach the legal retirement age.\n- Receive a disability allowance and reach the legal retirement age.\n- Receive social assistance and reach the legal retirement age."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "If none of the above applies, you must submit an application:\n- **Online:** Through [mypension.be](https://www.mypension.be/). Once submitted, you will receive a confirmation email if you provide your email address. Your application will appear under ‘My File’ during subsequent visits.\n- **Phone:** Call the Pension Line at **1765**, select Dutch, and press 3 and then 1.\n- **In Person:** At your local municipality office."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Payment Timeline\n- Payments start **the month after you reach the legal retirement age** if the process is automatic.\n- If you apply after reaching the retirement age, payments begin **the month following your application.**\n- For those without a recorded birth month, payments start on **August 1st of the year you reach the legal retirement age.**"
    },
    {
      "type": "source",
      "url": "https://www.mypension.be/"
    }
  ]
